metadata.feature_description: Caching mechanism for analytics data to improve performance

observations: The 'Analytics Data Caching' feature is classified as a 'Backend Service' with no UI location specified, meaning it operates at the infrastructure level without user-facing controls.

Code review of Services/CommunityAnalyticsController.cs reveals NO explicit caching implementation within the module - it delegates to IAnalyticsController from DotNetNuke.SocialLibrary.Components.Controllers, which is an external DNN framework component.
The CommunityAnalytics module contains NO cache-related code (searched for 'cache', 'Cache', 'caching', 'Caching' - no matches found in module files).
The Community Analytics panel fails to load with JavaScript error: 'TypeError: utility.serializeCustomDate is not a function' - preventing any UI interaction with the analytics dashboard.

DNN provides general caching configuration in Settings > Servers > Performance (Caching Provider: WebRequestCachingProvider, Module Cache Provider: Memory, Cache Setting: ModerateCaching), but these are system-wide settings, NOT specific Analytics Data Caching controls.
A general 'Clear Cache' button exists in Settings > Servers, but this clears ALL DNN cache, not specifically analytics cache.

The suggested test scenarios (cache initialization, cache expiration, cache invalidation, concurrent access, cache hit rates, cache size limits) cannot be tested via UI as there are NO UI elements to configure, monitor, or interact with analytics-specific caching.
Per testing philosophy: 'Feature exists in code but not visible in UI? Do NOT create a test for it.' - This backend service feature has no testable UI elements.

The feature dependency 'DNN Caching Framework' is confirmed present (WebRequestCachingProvider), but analytics-specific caching behavior is handled internally by the DNN framework without user-configurable options.

summary.pass_rate: N/A - No UI elements available to test this backend service feature
